<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-374-474  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 374 474.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  June 1989 v26 n6 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>War games change USAF communications games plan. (disasterpreparedness)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harker, Craig S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>During Exercise Salty Demo in 1985, the US Air ForceCommunications Command learned that few of itscommunications-restoral concepts survived this simulated war.andO;Restoral concepts developed at a Feb 1987 battle-damage conferenceof Allied Air Forces Central Europe have been applied tocommunications restoral.andP;  The restoral concept includes fourimperatives: design and develop new systems with built-inredundancy; stress the need for hardened or semi-hardenedfacilities construction; procure spares of essential equipment andcomponents; and resort to immediate repair only when redundancy,protection or replacement strategies have failed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Air Force. Communications CommandMilitaryDisaster PlanningTelecommunicationsCommunications ManagementSimulationBack-Up SystemsRepairRestoration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>